2026-07-03  Roman Senn  <roman.l.senn@gmail.com>

	Bug-fix pass on the QuickJS ↔ NanoVG binding.

	The fixes below were derived from a static read of nvgjs-module.[ch]
	and nvgjs-utils.[ch]. Every fix is covered by an entry in the new
	test-fixes.js harness — before the fixes 2/26 assertions failed
	(both symptoms of the misplaced-break bug); after the fixes all 26
	pass. Run with `qjsm test-fixes.js` against an installed nanovg.so.

	* nvgjs-module.c (nvgjs_tocolor):
	Clear the pending TypeError/RangeError left over by the failed
	4-element probe before attempting the 3-element (RGB-only, alpha=1)
	fallback. Previously a valid 3-element colour was accepted but the
	stale exception leaked into the next JS API call, sporadically
	throwing "expecting a Float32Array" from an unrelated site.

	* nvgjs-module.c (nvgjs_transform_function, TRANSFORM_MULTIPLY case):
	Move the misplaced `break` to the end of the case and reset `tmp` to
	identity, so nvgTransformMultiply actually runs. Previously the case
	skipped the multiply entirely and the unconditional post-switch
	nvgTransformPremultiply(mat, tmp) fired with `tmp` still holding the
	user's argument — making the instance method `.Multiply(m)` silently
	behave like `.Premultiply(m)`. Test coverage:
	  - Scale(2,3).Multiply(Translate(5,7)) now returns
	    [2,0,0,3, 5, 7] (previously [2,0,0,3, 10, 21]).
	  - .Multiply and .Premultiply now disagree on non-commutative pairs.

	* nvgjs-module.c (nvgjs_context_finalizer):
	Removed the "XXX: bug" marker and replaced with a comment documenting
	the ordering constraint: the finalizer intentionally does NOT call
	nvgDeleteGL[23] because it may run after the owning GL context
	(managed by the glfw module) has already been destroyed. Callers that
	want deterministic teardown must still call DeleteGL3(nvg) before
	closing the window — this is now an explicit contract rather than a
	silent leak.

	* nvgjs-module.c (CreateGL2): Fix `ctxc` typo → `ctx`. The
	NANOVG_GL2 code path is behind an #ifdef that is not currently set
	in CMakeLists.txt, so this was a latent build error; flipping the
	flag would previously have failed to compile.

	* nvgjs-module.c (BeginFrame): Change bitwise `|` to logical `||` in
	the JS_ToFloat64 chain for w/h/ratio so conversion errors
	short-circuit instead of stacking additional exceptions onto an
	already-pending one.

	* nvgjs-module.c (Context.ResetScissor): Add the missing
	`return JS_UNDEFINED;`. The non-void JS callback previously fell off
	the end of the function; the returned JSValue was whatever was in
	the return register — potentially a corrupted object handle.

	* nvgjs-module.c (Context.Text, Context.TextBox, Context.TextBounds,
	Context.TextBoxBounds):
	  - x, y (and w for TextBox/TextBoxBounds) converted with
	    JS_ToFloat64 into double, instead of JS_ToInt32 into int.
	    NanoVG's text APIs take floats; the old code silently truncated
	    fractional positions.
	  - If the optional `pos` argument is present but its int conversion
	    fails, propagate the exception (return JS_EXCEPTION and free the
	    duplicated CString) instead of ignoring the pending exception
	    and continuing.
	  - TextBoxBounds now null/undefined-guards `argv[4]` before trying
	    to convert it, matching the pattern in TextBounds.

	* nvgjs-module.c (nvgjs_paint_new):
	Free the malloc'd NVGpaint* on the JS_NewObjectClass failure path.
	Previously an out-of-memory or class-creation error leaked
	sizeof(NVGpaint) bytes on every call.

	* nvgjs-module.c (nvgjs_arraybuffer_free) [new], (ReadPixels):
	Introduced a small wrapper matching QuickJS's
	`JSFreeArrayBufferDataFunc` signature (rt, opaque, ptr) that
	delegates to js_free_rt(rt, ptr). ReadPixels now passes this wrapper
	instead of casting `js_free_rt` (which has arity 2) to a
	3-argument callback — undefined behaviour per ISO C, and portable
	only by accident of the SysV ABI on the currently-supported
	x86_64 target.

	* nvgjs-utils.c (nvgjs_iterator):
	Remove the shadowing `JSAtom iterator = ...` declaration inside the
	init block that had been hiding the outer static. Consequence of the
	shadow: the static was never assigned, every call to
	nvgjs_iterator() returned JS_ATOM_NULL (0) and leaked the newly
	created atom, and every iterable-input path
	(nvgjs_inputoutputarray, nvgjs_input) silently failed to recognise
	iterables — falling through to a TypeError. The unused
	`JSValue ret = JS_UNDEFINED;` local was also removed.

	* nvgjs-utils.c (nvgjs_inputarray, nvgjs_inputoutputarray,
	nvgjs_input):
	Explicitly clear the TypeError thrown by the initial
	nvgjs_outputarray probe before falling back to Array / iterator /
	property-map paths. Successful fallbacks previously returned 0 with
	a stale exception still on the context, which QuickJS then treated
	as if the entire wrapper function had thrown.

	* nvgjs-utils.c (nvgjs_inputobject, nvgjs_inputarray,
	nvgjs_inputiterator):
	Free per-element JSValues (and, for nvgjs_inputiterator, the outer
	iterator object) on the error-return paths.

	* nvgjs-utils.c (nvgjs_inputoutputarray):
	The final TypeError path previously leaked the JSCString returned by
	JS_ToCString and dereferenced NULL if the conversion itself failed.
	Now it stashes the pointer, uses "" as the fallback, and always
	frees the string.

	* nvgjs-module.h:
	Rename the exported prototype from `js_init_module_nanovg` (which
	matched no C definition) to `nvgjs_init_module`, and note the
	shared-library rename to `js_init_module` in a comment.

	* test-fixes.js [new]:
	Headless (no-GL) unit tests exercising the code paths above:
	  Group A — colour helpers (RGB / RGBA / RGBf / RGBAf / HSL / HSLA /
	    LerpRGBA / TransRGBA / TransRGBAf) — targets nvgjs_tocolor and
	    the util exception-clearing fixes.
	  Group B — DegToRad / RadToDeg.
	  Group C — Transform statics (Identity, Translate, Scale, Rotate).
	  Group D — Transform instance methods, specifically:
	    .Multiply must give mat := arg * mat
	    .Premultiply must give mat := mat * arg
	    They must disagree for non-commutative pairs.
	  Group E — TransformPoint.
	  Group F — Transform.TransformPoint instance.
	Assertions log a one-line message on failure and the runner exits
	non-zero if any test fails.

	* ChangeLog [new]:
	This file.
